checkGrid

boolean checkGrid()
Returns a 'boolean'. Returns 'true' if the grid contains a valid sudoku solution, returns 'false' otherwise. Checks all rows, columns, and subgrids of the grid object until an invalid entry is encountered. This mehthod is the backbone of the class.
